From: Matthew Vick <matthew.vick@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Oct 2014 05:10:18 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 40/97] fm10k: Check the host state when bringing the interface
 up
Patch-mainline: v3.18-rc1
Git-commit: 4d4191566fdd0e8990b2e8ab5ae819227c92892f
References: bsc#922855 FATE#318530

Set the flag to fetch the host state before kicking off the service task
that reads the host state when bringing the interface back up.

Signed-off-by: Matthew Vick <matthew.vick@intel.com>
Tested-by: Aaron Brown <aaron.f.brown@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Acked-by: David Chang <dchang@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/fm10k/fm10k_pci.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/fm10k/fm10k_pci.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/fm10k/fm10k_pci.c
@@ -1490,6 +1490,7 @@ void fm10k_up(struct fm10k_intfc *interf
 	netif_tx_start_all_queues(interface->netdev);
 
 	/* kick off the service timer */
+	hw->mac.get_host_state = 1;
 	mod_timer(&interface->service_timer, jiffies);
 }
 
